it.serendigity.other

Class Dynamite

  • java.lang.Object
    • it.serendigity.other.Dynamite

  • public class Dynamite
extends Object
    Provides ways to explode dynamite to blow up roadrunners.

    Try using the ACMESmartphone.zapRoadRunner(int) before resorting to blowDynamiteLoudBang(int). However, if you do have a lot of roadrunners, the zapRoadRunner method may not be efficient enough. You'll probably just want to resort to blowDynamiteLoudBang() to annihilate them all at once.

        public void blowDynamiteLoudBang(int fuseLength)
        Blows dynamite with a decibel level approximating that of a fog horn.

      • blowDynamiteSilentBang

        public void blowDynamiteSilentBang(int fuseLength)
        Blows dynamite with almost no sound at all (equivalent to a silencer on a gun).
        Parameters:
        fuseLength - the length of the fuse, which determines safety (silent bangs are just as deadly as loud bangs)
        See Also:
        blowDynamiteLoudBang(int), ACMESmartphone.zapRoadRunner(int)
